    "updated_at": "2013-07-07T19:15:33Z",
    "body": "I think I disagree with this. There's nothing about atomic ops that break the type system; they are only dangerous in conjunction with unsafe-shared-mutable-state. So you'll already have to have unsafe blocks if you're doing unsafe atomic ops.\n",
    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
