    "created_at": "2013-07-14T17:45:26Z",
    "updated_at": "2013-07-14T17:45:26Z",
    "body": "It is true that they are not good for much when used in otherwise-safe code. But that doesn't make them unsafe in their own right. Sort of like how creating a `*T` is fine, but dereferencing it is unsafe.\n\nI suppose they are just the intrinsics, not the interface of the `unstable::atomics` library, so it does not matter as much as I initially thought, since pretty much nobody except `unstable::atomics` should be using them directly.\n",
    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
