    "created_at": "2013-07-14T17:56:04Z",
    "updated_at": "2013-07-14T17:56:04Z",
    "body": "Think about it like this: An operation is `unsafe` iff the compiler cannot verify that an arbitrary use of the operation will not break type safety or memory safety. If we can reason about the operation to the extent that we're sure that no use of it will crash, there's no reason for it to be unsafe.\n",
    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
